'''Régis Ovion''' (born 3 March 1949) is a former French road racing cyclist.<ref name="ProCycling">{{cite web |url=http://www.procyclingstats.com/rider.php?id=167693 |title=Régis Ovion |accessdate=27 April 2014 |work=ProCyclingStats}}</ref> As an amateur he won the individual world title and the [[Tour de l'Avenir]] in 1971 and placed 15th in the [[Cycling at the 1972 Summer Olympics – Men's individual road race|road race]] at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]].<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ov/regis-ovion-1.html |title=Régis Ovion |accessdate=27 April 2014 |work=Sports Reference}}</ref> After the Olympics he turned professional and rode the [[Tour de France]] in 1973–78 and 1980–81 with the best result of tenth place in 1973.<ref name="CyclingArchives">{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingarchives.com/coureurfiche.php?coureurid=3248 |title=Régis Ovion |accessdate=27 April 2014 |work=Cycling Archives}}</ref>

